# Test Project From Effective Mobile

A check-ready REST API built with Django and Django REST Framework 

## Tech Stack

- **Python 3.12** / **Django 5.x**
- **Django REST Framework** — API layer
- **djangorestframework-simplejwt** — JWT authentication
- **drf-spectacular** — Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
- **SQLite** (development) 

---

## Architecture

Mostly
```
GenericView → Repository → ORM → Database
```

A few times
```
View → Service → Repository → ORM → Database
```

- **View | Generic** — handles HTTP, permissions, serialization
- **Service** — access logic
- **Repository** — database queries
- **ORM** — Django models

---

## Features

- Role-based access control (Admin / Manager / User / Guest)
- Role "Admin" has all previleges in all objects
- Role "Manager" has previleges in Create Update Read in objects, behind access rules and elements
- Role "User" can only read.
- Role "Guest" can't do anything.
- Swagger UI documentation

**Access Rules Schema**

The permission system is built on three entities:

- **Role** — a field on the User model (`admin`, `manager`, `user`, `guest`)
- **BusinessElement** — a catalog of protected resources (e.g. `order`, `product`)
- **AccessRules** — links a role + element to specific permissions (`can_read`, `can_create`, `can_update`, `can_delete`)

When a request hits a protected endpoint, `AccessService.has_permission(role, element, action)` looks up the matching `AccessRules` row and returns whether the action is allowed. If no rule exists, access is denied by default.

| Role       | Read  | Create | Update | Delete |
|------------|------ |--------|--------|--------|
| Admin      |  ✅  |   ✅   |  ✅   |   ✅   |
| Manage     |  ✅  |   ✅   |  ✅   |   ❌   |
| User       |  ✅  |   ❌   |  ❌   |   ❌   |
| Guest      |  ❌  |   ❌   |  ❌   |   ❌   |

If the user is unauthenticated → `401 Unauthorized`.
If authenticated but lacks permission → `403 Forbidden`.
---

## Default Roles After Registration

New users get the `guest` role by default. To test other roles, manually update `role` field via Django admin or shell.

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/tolipjonovqudratillo0423/Effective-Mobile
cd project

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

pip install -r requirements.txt

cp .venv.example .venv  # fill in your credentials

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate


python manage.py seed_access_rules
python manage.py runserver
```

### Environment Variables (.env)

```env
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key
DEBUG=True
ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME=100
REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME=1
```

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| POST | `/auth/register/`                      | Register new user | Public |
| POST | `/auth/login/`                         | Login, get JWT tokens | Public |
| GET | `/auth/profile/`                         | Look through his profile |
| PUT | `/auth/profile/`                         | Update profile |
| DELETE | `/auth/profile/`                         | Makes user inactive |

### Mock-data (Product)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/sales/product/`                       | List all open products |
| POST | `/sales/product/`                      | Create a product | 
| GET | `/sales/product/<int:pk>/`              | Get product's details |
| PATCH | `/sales/product/<int:pk>/`            | Partial Update of Product |
| PUT | `/sales/product/<int:pk>/`              |Full Update of Product |
| DELETE | `/sales/product/<int:pk>/`           | Delete Product |

### Mock-data (Product)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/sales/order/`                         | List all open projects |
| POST | `/sales/order/`                        | Create a order | 
| GET | `/sales/order/<int:pk>/`                | Get order's details |
| PATCH | `/sales/order/<int:pk>/`              | Partial Update of order |
| PUT | `/sales/order/<int:pk>/`                |Full Update of Profuct |
| DELETE | `/sales/order/<int:pk>/`             | Delete order |

### System_console (Business Elements)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/system_console/business_elements/`            | List all open business_elements |
| POST | `/system_console/business_elements/`           | Create a business_elements | 
| GET | `/system_console/business_elements/<int:pk>/`   | Get business_elements's details |
| PATCH | `/system_console/business_elements/<int:pk>/` | Partial Update of business_elements |
| PUT | `/system_console/business_elements/<int:pk>/`   |Full Update of business_elements |
| DELETE | `/system_console/business_elements/<int:pk>/`| Delete business_elements |



### System_console (Access Rules)
| Method | Endpoint | Description | Access |
|--------|----------|-------------|--------|
| GET | `/system_console/access_rules/`              | List all open access_rules |
| POST | `/system_console/access_rules/`             | Create a access_rules | 
| GET | `/system_console/access_rules/<int:pk>/`     | Get access_rules's details |
| PATCH | `/system_console/access_rules/<int:pk>/`   | Partial Update of access_rules |
| PUT | `/system_console/access_rules/<int:pk>/`     |Full Update of access_rules |
| DELETE | `/system_console/access_rules/<int:pk>/`  | Delete access_rules |

